WEBVTT

00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:33.136
The other slip of paper says,
"For my sake the world was created."

00:12:33.160 --> 00:12:36.280
Which is to say it's true
that I can't do everything,

00:12:37.040 --> 00:12:39.240
but I can surely do something.

00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:41.816
I can forgive.

00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:43.040
I can love.

00:12:43.560 --> 00:12:45.056
I can show up.

00:12:45.080 --> 00:12:46.696
I can protest.

00:12:46.720 --> 00:12:49.896
I can be a part of this conversation.

00:12:49.920 --> 00:12:52.776
We even now have a religious ritual,

00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:54.016
a posture,

00:12:54.040 --> 00:12:57.736
that holds the paradox
between powerlessness and power.

00:12:57.760 --> 00:12:58.976
In the Jewish community,

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:02.296
the only time of year
that we prostrate fully to the ground